---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Origin | Why Toyb Exists"
  description="Learn how Toyb emerged from the structural demands of building The Quantum Syndicate, where narrative complexity outgrew note-taking and required system-level control."
  canonical="/origin"
>
  <section
    id="origin-hero"
    class="hero origin-hero"
    aria-labelledby="origin-hero-title"
    data-reveal
    data-origin-section="hero"
  >
    <p class="origin-kicker">Origin</p>
    <h1 id="origin-hero-title" class="hero-title">
      The Quantum Syndicate
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-subtitle">
      The science-fiction narrative universe that made Toyb necessary.
    </p>
    <!-- TODO(origin-hero): expand only if the final editorial pass needs a shorter or longer opening frame. -->
    <div class="origin-hero__body">
      <p>
        Toyb did not begin as a software idea.<br />
        It began with a world.
      </p>
      <p>
        During the construction of The Quantum Syndicate, a complex narrative
        universe shaped by timelines, factions, technologies, memory, and
        causal links, one problem became clear: traditional tools were no
        longer enough.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="origin-hero__note">
      This page explains the product origin, not the project lore.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Origin hero call to actions">
      <a
        class="button button-primary"
        href="/#preview"
        data-track="cta_origin_hero_preview"
      >
        See how Toyb works
      </a>
      <a
        class="button"
        href="/#waitlist-title"
        data-track="cta_origin_hero_early_access"
      >
        Get early access
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Section
    id="origin-introduction"
    title="Origin in context"
    subtitle="Toyb emerged while a large narrative project started demanding system-level control rather than better note storage."
  >
    <div class="origin-grid" data-origin-section="introduction">
      <article class="origin-panel origin-panel--intro-copy">
        <p>
          The Quantum Syndicate was the project context in which Toyb's
          requirements became visible. As the world expanded, the work stopped
          behaving like a set of isolated documents and started behaving like a
          system under pressure.
        </p>
        <p>
          This page exists to explain that origin in practical terms. Toyb did
          not come from generic software ideation. It came from the structural
          demands of keeping a complex narrative world coherent over time.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside class="origin-panel origin-panel--aside" aria-label="Content map">
        <h3>Content map</h3>
        <ul class="origin-outline origin-outline--intro">
          <li>the project conditions that exposed the workflow gap</li>
          <li>the coherence problem behind the product</li>
          <li>the shift from narrative workload to system design</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    id="origin-problem"
    title="The problem was not writing. It was maintaining coherence."
    subtitle="What was missing was not a place to collect material. It was a way to sustain the structure."
  >
    <div class="origin-grid" data-origin-section="problem">
      <article class="origin-panel origin-panel--problem-copy">
        <p>
          The Quantum Syndicate was never just a collection of notes.
          It was a connected system.
        </p>
        <p>
          As the project expanded, the difficulty was no longer simply writing
          scenes or preserving ideas.
        </p>
        <p>
          The real problem was maintaining coherence within a narrative
          structure that kept evolving.
        </p>
        <p>
          Folders, scattered notes, separate documents, and improvised schemas
          could preserve fragments.
        </p>
        <p>They could not truly sustain the structure.</p>
      </article>

      <aside
        class="origin-panel origin-panel--aside origin-panel--problem-system"
        aria-label="Narrative interdependencies"
      >
        <ul class="origin-outline origin-outline--problem">
          <li>Characters influenced events.</li>
          <li>Events reshaped timelines.</li>
          <li>
            Factions produced consequences that extended from one narrative arc
            to another.
          </li>
          <li>
            Technologies changed the political, identity, and historical
            context of the world.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    id="origin-system-design"
    title="From narrative complexity to system design."
    subtitle="When complexity outgrew manual handling, the problem became operational."
  >
    <div class="origin-split" data-origin-section="system-design">
      <article class="origin-panel origin-panel--system-design-copy">
        <p>
          At a certain point, the bottleneck became obvious.
        </p>
        <p>
          The problem was not a lack of imagination.
          It was the absence of operational control.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside
        class="origin-panel origin-panel--aside"
        aria-label="Operational requirements that emerged"
      >
        <p class="origin-panel__lead">
          What was needed was a workspace where narrative elements could behave
          as connected entities rather than scattered documents:
        </p>
        <ul class="origin-outline origin-outline--system-design">
          <li>characters linked to plots</li>
          <li>events anchored to timelines</li>
          <li>factions traced across narrative arcs</li>
          <li>dependencies made visible</li>
          <li>
            contradictions identified before they became structural damage
          </li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>

    <div class="origin-bridge">
      <p>
        Toyb emerged from that need.
      </p>
      <p>
        It was designed to make complex narrative systems legible, navigable,
        and manageable over time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    id="origin-why-it-matters"
    title="Why this matters"
    subtitle="Toyb was built for creators dealing with systems that exceed note-taking."
  >
    <div class="origin-panel origin-panel--why-it-matters" data-origin-section="why-it-matters">
      <div class="origin-why-it-matters__copy">
        <p>
          Toyb exists for creators working on projects that exceed note-taking.
        </p>
        <p>
          If your work includes chronology, relationships, factions,
          dependencies, latent contradictions, and structural growth over time,
          then the challenge is no longer just writing.
        </p>
        <p>It is maintaining coherence without losing control.</p>
        <p>That is exactly the problem Toyb was built to solve.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Why this matters call to actions">
        <a
          class="button button-primary"
          href="/#preview"
          data-track="cta_origin_why_it_matters_preview"
        >
          See how Toyb works
        </a>
        <a
          class="button"
          href="/#waitlist-title"
          data-track="cta_origin_why_it_matters_early_access"
        >
          Get early access
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <section
    id="origin-cta"
    class="section origin-cta"
    aria-labelledby="origin-cta-title"
    data-reveal
    data-origin-section="cta"
  >
    <div class="origin-cta__inner">
      <div class="origin-cta__copy">
        <h2 id="origin-cta-title">Built from a real narrative challenge.</h2>
        <p>
          Toyb began with one world.
        </p>
        <p>
          It was built for creators who need structure, continuity, and control
          as their projects grow in complexity.
        </p>
        <p>
          If your work extends beyond isolated notes, Toyb was designed to help
          the system hold together.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Origin closing call to actions">
        <a
          class="button button-primary"
          href="/#waitlist-title"
          data-track="cta_origin_footer_early_access"
        >
          Get early access
        </a>
        <a class="button" href="/#preview" data-track="cta_origin_footer_preview">
          Jump to preview
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .origin-hero {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-4);
    }

    .origin-hero .hero-title {
      max-width: 18ch;
    }

    .origin-kicker {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--text-xs);
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 74%, var(--text));
    }

    .origin-hero__body {
      max-width: 60ch;
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-3);
    }

    .origin-hero__body p {
      margin: 0;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 84%, transparent);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.72;
    }

    .origin-hero__note {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--text-sm);
      line-height: 1.58;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 68%, transparent);
    }

    .origin-grid,
    .origin-split {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-4);
    }

    .origin-panel,
    .origin-card,
    .origin-cta__inner {
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 74%, transparent);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
    }

    .origin-panel,
    .origin-card {
      padding: var(--space-5);
    }

    .origin-panel {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-3);
    }

    .origin-panel--intro-copy p,
    .origin-panel--problem-copy p {
      margin: 0;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 84%, transparent);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.72;
    }

    .origin-panel--system-design-copy p,
    .origin-bridge p {
      margin: 0;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 84%, transparent);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.72;
    }

    .origin-panel h3,
    .origin-card h3 {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 92%, transparent);
    }

    .origin-panel--aside {
      align-content: start;
      background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 68%, var(--bg));
    }

    .origin-outline {
      margin: 0;
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.8rem;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 80%, transparent);
      font-size: 0.98rem;
      line-height: 1.62;
    }

    .origin-outline--problem {
      padding-left: 1rem;
      gap: 1rem;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 86%, transparent);
    }

    .origin-outline--intro {
      padding-left: 1rem;
      gap: 0.9rem;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 84%, transparent);
    }

    .origin-outline--problem li::marker {
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 72%, var(--text));
    }

    .origin-panel__lead {
      margin: 0;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 84%, transparent);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.72;
    }

    .origin-panel--why-it-matters {
      gap: var(--space-4);
    }

    .origin-why-it-matters__copy {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-3);
      max-width: 60ch;
    }

    .origin-why-it-matters__copy p {
      margin: 0;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 84%, transparent);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.72;
    }

    .origin-outline--system-design {
      padding-left: 1rem;
      gap: 0.82rem;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 86%, transparent);
    }

    .origin-outline--system-design li::marker {
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 72%, var(--text));
    }

    .origin-card-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-4);
    }

    .origin-card {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-3);
      min-height: 100%;
    }

    .origin-bridge {
      border-left: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 34%, transparent);
      padding-left: var(--space-4);
      max-width: 58rem;
    }

    .origin-cta {
      margin-top: var(--space-8);
    }

    .origin-cta__inner {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-4);
      padding: var(--space-5);
    }

    .origin-cta__copy {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-3);
      max-width: 42rem;
    }

    .origin-cta__copy h2 {
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 2.6vw, 2.2rem);
    }

    .origin-cta__copy p {
      margin: 0;
      color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 84%, transparent);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.72;
    }

    @media (min-width: 48rem) {
      .origin-grid {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.7fr) minmax(18rem, 0.9fr);
      }

      .origin-split {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }

      .origin-card-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }

      .origin-cta__inner {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.45fr) auto;
        align-items: end;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    import { track } from "../lib/analytics";

    const pagePath = window.location.pathname;
    const trackedScrollDepths = new Set<number>();
    const depthSteps = [25, 50, 75, 100];

    // TODO(origin-analytics): enrich payloads when consent-aware analytics is enabled.
    track("origin_page_view", { path: pagePath });

    const trackScrollDepth = () => {
      const scrollableHeight =
        document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
      const progress =
        scrollableHeight <= 0
          ? 100
          : Math.round((window.scrollY / scrollableHeight) * 100);

      depthSteps.forEach((depth) => {
        if (progress < depth || trackedScrollDepths.has(depth)) return;
        trackedScrollDepths.add(depth);
        track("origin_scroll_depth", { path: pagePath, depth });
      });
    };

    trackScrollDepth();
    window.addEventListener("scroll", trackScrollDepth, { passive: true });

    const trackedSections = new Set<string>();
    const sectionTargets = document.querySelectorAll("[data-origin-section]");

    if ("IntersectionObserver" in window) {
      const sectionObserver = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries, observer) => {
          entries.forEach((entry) => {
            if (!entry.isIntersecting) return;
            const sectionName = entry.target.getAttribute("data-origin-section");
            if (!sectionName || trackedSections.has(sectionName)) return;
            trackedSections.add(sectionName);
            track("origin_section_view", {
              path: pagePath,
              section: sectionName,
            });
            observer.unobserve(entry.target);
          });
        },
        { threshold: 0.45 },
      );

      sectionTargets.forEach((target) => sectionObserver.observe(target));
    }
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
